Selenium Automation Testing with ChatGPT
What is Selenium?
Selenium is an open-source automation testing tool used to automate web browsers.

Selenium Suite
Tool	                Purpose
Selenium IDE	      Record & Playback
Selenium WebDriver	Browser automation using code
Selenium Grid	      Parallel execution
Selenium Manager	  Automatically manages browser drivers (Selenium 4.6+)
_________________________________________________________
Selenium WebDriver Workflow
Start Browser
      ↓
Navigate to URL
      ↓
Locate Element
      ↓
Perform Action
      ↓
Validate Result
      ↓
Close Browser
________________________________________
Selenium Locators
Locators identify elements on a web page.

Locator	        Example
id	            id="username"
name	          name="email"
className	      class="btn"
tagName          	input
linkText	        Login
partialLinkText    	Log
cssSelector	      input#username
xpath	            //input[@id='username']

_____________________________________________

Best Practice Order
ID
Name
CSS Selector
XPath
__________________________
XPath
Relative XPath ✅
//input[@id='username']

Absolute XPath ❌
/html/body/div[2]/div/form/input

Common XPath Examples
By Attribute:
//input[@name='email']

Contains:
//button[contains(text(),'Login')]

Starts With:
//input[starts-with(@id,'user')]

Text:
//button[text()='Submit']

Multiple Attributes:
//input[@type='text' and @name='email']

Parent:
//label[text()='Email']/parent::div

Following Sibling:
//label[text()='Email']/following-sibling::input
