___________________________________
Waits (Very Important)
Hard-coded waits often make tests unreliable.

Implicit Wait
Applies globally.
ex.driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(Duration.ofSeconds(10));

Explicit Wait ⭐
Recommended for most synchronization scenarios.
ex.
WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, Duration.ofSeconds(10));
wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOf(element));

Fluent Wait
Allows custom polling intervals and ignored exceptions.
Use when elements appear unpredictably.
